summary: SummaryThe MAC iconic Lip Liner does way more than draw the line. Praised by Pros and loved by you, this must-have in every makeup bag features a smooth and creamy texture to shape, fill or line lips – without the drags or skips
details: DetailsBenefitsUltra-versatile formulaSmooth and creamy textureWide range of Artist-approved shadesDesigned to complement all M·A·C lip colours to create limitless combosWon't skip or dragApplies quickly and preciselyFormulated WithoutFormaldehydeHydroquinoneTriclosanCoal TarTolueneSiliconeParabensMineral OilItem 2635489How To UseBEFORE LIPSTICK:To naturally define lips, start by outlining the Cupid's bow. Then, switch to the outer corners of upper lips and draw inward until you connect the lines at the centre.To enhance your lips and create a fuller-looking effect, trace along your upper lip line while gradually overlining beyond the natural border of your lips.To create a contoured lip look, choose a shade deeper than your Lipstick to outline lips. Then, fill in the centre of lips with the lighter Lipstick, slightly overlapping with your liner. Blend with a 316S Brush to create a natural-looking gradient.AFTER LIPSTICK:To add extra definition, line lips after applying your Lipstick.WITH LIPGLASSOutline or fill in lips completely, then layer on Lipglass for a high-shine look.LINER ONLY:Shade and fill in lips.IngredientsC10-18 Triglycerides, Talc, Hydrogenated Vegetable Oil, Caprylic / Capric Triglyceride, Rhus Succedanea (Japan) Fruit Wax, Tocopherol, Ascorbyl Palmitate. May Contain: Mica, Titanium Dioxide (CI 77891), Iron Oxides (CI 77491), Iron Oxides (CI 77499), Iron Oxides (CI 77492), Bismuth Oxychloride (CI 77163), Blue 1 Lake (CI 42090), Carmine (CI 75470), Manganese Violet (CI 77742), Red 6 (CI 15850), Red 21 (CI 45380), Red 30 (CI 73360), Red 7 Lake (CI 15850), Red 28 Lake (CI 45410), Yellow 5 Lake (CI 19140), Yellow 6 Lake (CI 15985).Shipping & Coupon RestrictionsThis brand is excluded from most Ulta Beauty coupons.See brand eligibility details
how_to_use: BEFORE LIPSTICK:To naturally define lips, start by outlining the Cupid's bow. Then, switch to the outer corners of upper lips and draw inward until you connect the lines at the centre.To enhance your lips and create a fuller-looking effect, trace along your upper lip line while gradually overlining beyond the natural border of your lips.To create a contoured lip look, choose a shade deeper than your Lipstick to outline lips. Then, fill in the centre of lips with the lighter Lipstick, slightly overlapping with your liner. Blend with a 316S Brush to create a natural-looking gradient.AFTER LIPSTICK:To add extra definition, line lips after applying your Lipstick.WITH LIPGLASSOutline or fill in lips completely, then layer on Lipglass for a high-shine look.LINER ONLY:Shade and fill in lips.

reviews.headline: Great Color and Liner
reviews.comments: I like this lip liner a lot - was recommended to me by professional makeup artist, i thought $25 was a lot for this pencil, but the quality is unparalleled for me. It glides on smoothly without having to press too hard, it stays on for hours and hours (even after eating and drinking). The pigment great, high quality - a little goes a long way - i have a feeling this pencil will last me years. Bought the liner in color "Whirl" and then bought the MAC lipstick in color "Mehr" (both colors on in photo). Colors stay even in hot southern heat of summer - dont seem to sunk into my fine lip lines.

reviews.headline: Bought this 10+ times
reviews.comments: Ive bought so many of these its stupid lol. Theyre my fav liner. I have tried a lot of liners, this one is the best for me. I have really dry skin and lips and it applies great.

reviews.headline: Holy grail
reviews.comments: I had to come on here and leave a review for cool spice. I have always used anywhere caffeine and wherever walnut but one was too orange and the other a bit too pink. cool spice is right in between the too and its just the perfect brown/nude/mauve/pink shade. im sooo particular about lip liner colors and this is finally what I was looking for. I wish the staying power was a bit better but either way I will definitely repurchase this.

reviews.headline: Cherry lipliner!
reviews.comments: Mac's lipliners are the only liners I use. They stay on and help lipstick last longer. I use the Cherry lipliner with every red and bright pink lipsticks I have. Highly recommend

reviews.headline: Holy Grail Lip Liner
reviews.comments: This has been my go to lip liner for over 20 years. It's the perfect shade of reddish brown. I can apply heavier or lighter depending on which lipstick or gloss I'm pairing it with, and it glides on smooth and effortlessly. Absolutely love the MAC mahogany lip pencil!

reviews.headline: This lip liner is my old time favorite.

reviews.comments: purchased the shade oak. I have a light-medium complexion. it is a beautiful natural-looking, your-lips-but-better neutral beige brown. it lasts a while and glides on quite nicely. it feels like a sturdy pencil, too.

faceoff_positive.comments:
I came on the site today to reorder a lipstick that had run low, and decided to check my "Favorites" list to see if there was anything there that I needed. And lo and behold an old friend reappeared - Stone lip pencil. I thought I must be seeing things. But no, it's there. And it's not marked as a limited edition.

Since it was discontinued several years ago, I've searched high and low for a replacement. But nothing was ever quite right. For the last year I had to use an EYE LINER to try and copy the color. Yes, an eye liner. I became desperate.

This was the perfect color for me to line my lips. It magically seemed to make my lips seem fuller (probably since it seems to almost mimics a very light shadow - thus giving the allusion of fuller lips). It also tones down brighter shades and turns pinks and nudes into colors that seem natural, healthy and beautiful. Some people may be turned off because it is described as grey muted taupe. But it is a truly natural looking color. Just not as yellow or orange as most "natural" or "beige" liners tend to be.

I ordered the maximum number that I was allowed with the largest smile on my face. PLEASE, PLEASE NEVER DISCONTINUE THIS AGAIN.
faceoff_positive.headline: Stone is back?!?!?! THANK YOU THANK YOU THANK YOU

faceoff_negative.comments:
I've been buying the MAC lip pencil in Stripdown for over ten years. It's the only product I use to line and fill in my lips. The color closely matches my natural lip color and every pencil I've purchased through the years has never varied in color or consistency, its always been exactly the same. I just received an order of two Stripdown lip pencils and something has definitely changed. The color is different. It's more of a matte light brown and the consistency is awful. It's soft not firm. It's more like a lipstick consistency. I can't use it to line my lips because it smudges, is messy and the tip breaks off with very minimal pressure. Both lip pencils I received are this same new product. 

Did I just get a bad batch or has my favorite color lip pencil really changed? I'm so disappointed. 

Has anyone else experienced this problem?
faceoff_negative.headline: PRODUCT HAS CHANGED
